response.text:
The clinical trial NCT02838420 (ALESIA) compared alectinib and crizotinib as first-line treatments for ALK-positive non-small-cell lung cancer in Asian patients. The study found that alectinib was more effective than crizotinib.

Based on the study results, the less effective regimen ingredient in this trial was crizotinib.

INGREDIENT: CRIZOTINIB
